        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 12:38AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1238 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Cushing, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Sand Springs...                   Keystone State Park...
Silver City...                    Drumright...
Mannford...                       Sapulpa...
Oilton...                         Kellyville...
Kiefer...                         Tulsa...

This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 199 and 218.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for
northeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
